Sentencas: The commercialization of Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) has always been limited by the poor catalytic activity and the severe degradation of cathode in the intermediate and low operating temperature.
Titulo: Effects of Gd0.8Ce0.2O1.9-δ coating with different thickness on electrochemical performance and long-term stability of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode in SOFCs

Sentencas: Here we report a Gd0.8Ce0.2O1.9-delta (GDC) coated La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) composite cathode material, which can significantly improve the electrochemical performance and durability of LSCF cathode.
Titulo: Effects of Gd0.8Ce0.2O1.9-δ coating with different thickness on electrochemical performance and long-term stability of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode in SOFCs

Sentencas: The effects of different GDC coating thickness on the electrochemical performance and long-term working stability of LSCF cathode are investigated, and the optimal coating thickness is established.
Titulo: Effects of Gd0.8Ce0.2O1.9-δ coating with different thickness on electrochemical performance and long-term stability of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode in SOFCs

Sentencas: The polarization impedance of GDC coated LSCF (LSCF@GDC) cathode with 9 nm of GDC coating is 0.08 U cm(2) at 800 degrees C, which is only one quarter of that of the raw LSCF cathode, and the degradation rate of constant current polarization with 100 mA cm(-2) is only 0.42%/100 h at 700 degrees C, which is far less than that of the raw LSCF cathode.
Titulo: Effects of Gd0.8Ce0.2O1.9-δ coating with different thickness on electrochemical performance and long-term stability of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode in SOFCs

Sentencas: The X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS) results show that the degree of Sr segregation decreases with the increase of the thickness of the coated GDC layer.
Titulo: Effects of Gd0.8Ce0.2O1.9-δ coating with different thickness on electrochemical performance and long-term stability of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode in SOFCs

Sentencas: The potential LSCF@GDC composite material is expected to increase the operability of SOFCs and accelerate its commercialization.
Titulo: Effects of Gd0.8Ce0.2O1.9-δ coating with different thickness on electrochemical performance and long-term stability of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode in SOFCs
